General Education Requirement for Undergraduate Students ,93," Important News about ""General Education Requirement"" for Undergraduate Students  
The regulation for the General Education Requirements has been changed/updated from time to time.  Please be aware of these changes, as they may affect your course selection, the study path, and the graduation.   
For example,
For students admitted into NDHU on and before 100 School Year (2011 Summer),  
Total credits for each category in the General Education Requirements are:
　　1. Languages　　　　　: 12 credits
　　2. Arts and Humanities　 : 9 credits
　　3. Social Sciences　　　 : 9 credits
　　4. Math and the Sciences : 9 credits
　　5. Physical Education　　: 4 credits, including Physical Education 1, 2, 3, and 4
Total required credits for Arts and Humanities, Social Sciences, and Mathematics and the Sciences fields must be at least 27 credits.
For students admitted into NDHU on 101 School Year (2012 Summer), 
Total credits for each category in the General Education Requirements are:
　　1. Languages　　　　　: 12 credits
　　2. Arts and Humanities　 : 8 credits or above
　　3. Social Sciences　　　 : 8 credits or above
　　4. Math and the Sciences : 8 credits or above
　　5. Physical Education　　: 4 credits, including Physical Education 1, 2, 3, and 4
Total required credits for Arts and Humanities, Social Sciences, and Mathematics and the Sciences fields still must be at least 27 credits.
Since 102 School Year (2012 Summer), the General Education has expended into Core Curriculum Requirements
Total credits for Core Curriculum Requirements become:
　　1. Languages (9 credits total; 6 credits for Mandarin Chinese and 3 credits for Elective Foreign Languages),
　　2. Physical Education (4 credits total),
　　3. Service Learning (2 credits total),
　　4. Elective Core Courses (28 credits total).
Students may decide for themselves the most applicable version of the University Core Curriculum Requirements to count course credits toward graduation in the first semester of the final study year. 
The selected version of requirements does not have to be of the same year as that of the course requirements of students’ majors.
 The Department of General Education and the Department of CSIE have summarized all the rules and the regulations. You must read and understand them.  
Summarized Files are here:
NDHU_General_Education_Requirements_for_2011_School_Year.pdf 
NDHU_General_Education_Requirements_for_2012_School_Year.pdf
NDHU_Core_Curriculum_Requirements_starts_from_2013_School_Year.pdf 
NDHU_Core_Curriculum_Requirements_2013_School_Year.ppt (ppt file from General Education Department) 
NDHU_Core_Curriculum_Requirements_2013_School_Year_ChineseFull_Version.ppt (ppt file from General Education Department) 
