Important Announcement about the 2014 FALL Tuition & Fee Payment ,93,"Dear Current Students,
It is your responsibility to PAY OFF all your Tuition and Fee Balance and to complete the On-Line Registration Process before the Registration Day.   
According to NDHU’s FALL 2014 Academic Calendar, the tuition/fee payment period is 9/18~9/19.
The FALL Semester of 2014 starts on 9/17 (Wednesday).
The school will not mail copies of payment sheets to you. The Payment sheet for Tuition and Fees can be printed at  Taiwan Bank Student Payment System (https://school.bot.com.tw/twbank.net/index.aspx?pgid=3) .  We have taught you on how to print the payment sheet and to pay.  If you still have question, please let us know.   
If you have special circumstance (for example: cannot pay on time, not back to Taiwan yet, waiting for scholarship process …etc.), you should apply a written “Postpone Request ( get the form here )  ” to school and submit it to the CSIE Department Office ASAP, no later than 9/15. The written postpone request will be reviewed by the Department Chairman and the School Officers.  There is NO guarantee on the result of the request. If the request is granted, the latest payment due day may be extended to 10/9. (as 14 working days after the Registration Day). 
If the circumstance is extraordinary, you should make a written request of the “Installment Payment Plan ( get the form here ) ” to school and submit it to the CSIE Department Office ASAP, no later than 9/15. The written postpone request will be reviewed by the Department Chair and School Officers. There is NO guarantee on the result of the request. If the request is granted, the latest payment due day may be extended to 1/5 (as 1 week prior to the final exam and the last day of withdrawing the semester). 
Please Note 1: If you do not pay on-time as promised in Installment Payment Plan, or do not PAY OFF all your Tuition and Fee Balance by the last day, you WILL be expelled from NDHU, and the result will affect your future study. 
Please Note 2: NDHU Student Group Insurance Fee is combined into the Tuition and Fee balance.  In order to protect yourself,  you must pay this fee within 30 days after semester begins.  Otherwise, you will lose the protection for the entire semester.  This requirement applys to both ""postpone"" and ""installment"" students. 
This message is a comprehensive combination from the following Guideline and Regulation: 
Postpone Request / Installment Payment Plan Request (both Chinese & English) 學雜費延緩 / 分期繳交申請書 :
 http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/files/14-1006-58085,r1067-1.php 
Instruction on How to fill this Postpone Request : 
 instruction_on_tuition_postpone_intallment_plan_request.pdf 
NDHU’s Fall 2013~2014 Academic Calendar (in English) : 
 http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/img/946/102calendar_en.pdf   
Guideline of handling the delayed payment (in Chinese) 延誤繳交學雜費之處理原則 :  http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/attach/73/pta_26721_8919060_587... 
NDHU 2013 Student Group Insurance Guideline (in Chinese) 102學年度學生團體保險須知 :  http://www.student.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/7/1007/attach/2/pta_26307_504296_...
NDHU Academic Regulation (in Chinese) 東華大學學則 : 
http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/attach/95/pta_21805_673905_9227...
Dept of CSIE
