					2. Only 1 course from the same course group can be counted as the required credits of the program, although all credits are counted for graduation. Students must decide where the course credits will be counted. If graduate-level courses are counted
					for undergraduate programs or for graduation, they cannot be counted again for the master’s programs.
					3. For undergraduate students—when studying a graduate-level course with the same name, even though it is offered in different graduate programs (e.g. master’s, executive-master’s, doctoral), is deemed as the same-name course of this program.
			
