2013 Fall Semester Mid-Term Withdraw (by 11/22 5pm),93,"All, 
If you need to make a mid-term withdraw for a course, please start considering this policy:
1. The last date to withdraw a class of 2013 Fall Semester is Friday, 11/22, 5pm.  The system will close at 5:00 pm sharp.
2. Login into the Course Selection System (選課系統, http://web.ndhu.edu.tw/subjsele/activex_sele.htm ),
   2-1 select a class to be withdraw,
   2-2 print out the withdraw sheet,
   2-3 ask class teacher to sign,
   2-4 ask mentor teacher to sign,
   2-5 get departmental seal,
   2-6 return the sheet to Course Administrative Department. 
3. You only allow to withdraw 1 course during the mid-term withdraw period.  The course you withdrawed will have a ""W"" mark on your transcript, but will not be calculated into your GPA.  
4. Please consider your student status and scholarship qualification (minimum 9 credits) after withdraw.
5. No money refund of the withdraw course.
6. See the NDHU's Regulation of the Withdraw (http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/files/14-1006-14817,r1065-1.php )
If you have any question, please come to see me ASAP.
Dept of CSIE
