Important Announcement about the Tuition & Fee Payment,93,"Dear current students,
It is your responsibility to PAY OFF all your Tuition and Fee Balance and to complete the On-Line Registration process before the Registration Day.   As planned on the NDHU’s Fall 2013 Academic Calendar, the tuition/fee payment period is 8/22~9/13. 
The school will not mail copies of payment sheets. Payment sheet for Tuition and other Fees can be printed at: https://school.bot.com.tw/twbank.net/index.aspx?pgid=3 between 8/22~9/13, 2013.  You may check http://mis.ndhu.edu.tw/charge/sop2.pdf (in Chinese) for instructions on how to print the payment sheet. 
If you neglect to complete the payment and registration procedure by 9/13, you are in danger to be expelled from NDHU, and the result will affect your future study. 
If you have special circumstance (for example: cannot pay on time, not back to Taiwan yet, waiting for scholarship process…etc.), you should make a written “Postpone Request ( get the form here ) ” to school and submit it to the CSIE Department Office ASAP, no later than 9/10. The written postpone request will be reviewed by the Department Chair and School Officers. There is NO guarantee on the result of the request. If the request is granted, the latest payment due day may be extended to 10/7. (as 14 working days after the Registration Day). 
If the circumstance is extraordinary, you should make a written request of the “Installment Payment Plan ( get the form here) ” to school and submit it to the CSIE Department Office ASAP, no later than 9/10. The written postpone request will be reviewed by the Department Chair and School Officers. There is NO guarantee on the result of the request. If the request is granted, the latest payment due day may be extended to 12/30 (as 1 week prior to the final exam and the last day of withdrawing the semester). 
Please Note 1: If you do not pay on-time as promised in Installment Payment Plan, or do not PAY OFF all your Tuition and Fee Balance by the last day, you WILL be expelled from NDHU, and the result will affect your future study. 
Please Note 2: NDHU Student Group Insurance Fee is combined into the Tuition and Fee balance.  In order to protect yourself,  you must pay this fee within 30 days after semester begins.  Otherwise, you will lose the protection for the entire semester.  This requirement applys to both ""postpone"" and ""installment"" students.   
This message is a comprehensive combination from the following Guideline and Regulation: 
Postpone Request / Installment Payment Plan Request (in Chinse) 學雜費延緩 / 分期繳交申請書  http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/files/14-1006-58085,r1067-1.php    Instruction on How to fill this Postpone Request / Installment Payment Plan Request PDF file is included at the bottom of this announcement.
NDHU’s Fall 2013 Academic Calendar (in English)  http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/img/946/102calendar_en.pdf . 
Guideline of handling the delayed payment (in Chinese) 延誤繳交學雜費之處理原則  http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/attach/73/pta_26721_8919060_58792.pdf 
NDHU 2013 Student Group Insurance Guideline (in Chinese) 102學年度學生團體保險須知http://www.student.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/7/1007/attach/2/pta_26307_504296_60386.pdf
NDHU Academic Regulation (in Chinese) 東華大學學則 http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/ezfiles/6/1006/attach/95/pta_21805_673905_92277.pdf
Dept of CSIE
 
 
",Important Announcement about the Tuition & Fee Payment,08/29/2013 - 04:06,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/1085,1085,English
"If you did not pre-select the course at the end of the last semester, please read !",93,"Dear All, 
If you did not pre-select the course at the end of the last semester, you need to fill out this request form ( http://www.aa.ndhu.edu.tw/files/14-1006-14625,r1067-1.php ) in order to regain the course selection privilege.
After signed by your adviser and the department chairman, approved by the Academic Affair office, and see the review result, then, you are allowed to select the classes during the ""Courses Add / Drop / Selection week (9/23~9/26)"" .
You need to submit the Request Form to the CSIE Office before 9/14 (Thursday).  
Dept of CSIE
