2013 NDHU Graduation Ceremory This Saturday 6/8 ,93,"All, 
This is the activity guideline for the Graduation Ceremony this Saturday 6/8.  No matter you are the ""graduating student"" or the ""viewing guest"", you can follow this guideline as well.
(0.) Graduating Students: Wear your Graduation Gown, Scarf, Hat and Tassel.
(1.) 9:00am, All CSIE students are gathering at Engineering Building II, A337 room for preparation.
(2.) 09:30am, All CSIE students move to Engineering Building II, Lecture Hall II, for CSIE-Departmental level ceremony
(3.) 10:00am, Each student is called and required to walk on stage, chairman will move your hat's tassel from one side to another side, indicate you are graduating.  
(4.) 11:00am, Dismissed for Lunch, come back around 1pm for NDHU whole school-level ceremony.
(5.) 1:00~1:30pm, 
For Sambou and Riska, report at back of Gym building, you both have special seats due to you special status.
For Hery, and all CSIE students, will meet at 1st floor of Engineering Building II, near the ""A"" side of the building, then we will walk to Gym building together.
(6.) Caution !! The NDHU Graduate Ceremony is located in Gym building  !!   Not the same place as last year !! 
(7.) 2:10pm NDHU Graduate Ceremony starts.  All visitors and guests should seat on the 2nd floor of the Gym building.  
Enjoy this great event !
Dept of CSIE
