NDHU CSIE English Proficiency Requirement for Graduate Students  2013.05.07,93,"國立東華大學資訊工程學系研究生英語能力畢業標準實施辦法
English Proficiency Requirement for Graduate Students
Department of Computer Science & Information Engineering
National Dong Hwa University

Original requirement was listed in various graduate rules and regulations
Separated out as this article on 2013.01.15
Revised by Graduate Study Committee Meeting on 2013.05.07
 
 

 In order to enhance the competitiveness for employment and advanced study, this Requirement has been established to address the English Proficiency for all CSIE’s Graduate Students
 All graduate students must fulfill at least one of the requirements listed below; while those with degree from English-Spoken Countries may be exempted from the requirements.  The test date should be within 4 years prior to entering NDHU or while studying in NDHU.  Students must submit the original certification to verify.
 Master Students (including Master program, Network & Multimedia program, International Master program) :：
All master students should acquire at least one of the following English Proficiency certifications before graduation.  The test date should be within 4 years prior to entering NDHU or while studying in NDHU.  Students must submit the original certification to verify.


TOEFL iBT score 61 and above (TOEFL paper version PBT/ ITP score 500 and above) /
TOEIC score 600 and above /
GEPT (The General English Proficiency Test) Intermediate Level Second Stage, or High-Intermediate Level First Stage, or above (全民英檢，中級複試或中高級初試以上) /
Other equivalent official English proficiency exams offered in/outside of NDHU campus. (See Appendix #1)

Student may take the following English courses from either groups as the alternative of requirements:

Courses offered by the English Department, related to Listening, Communication, Oral Training, Reading, English Writing or Technical Writing, Composition,  Translating, or English for Science and Technology with 3 credits and graded B-  or above.
Courses offered by the General Education Department, related to Listening, Communication, Oral Training, Reading, English Writing or Technical Writing, Composition,  Translating, or English for Science and Technology, level (II) or above, with 3 credits and graded B+  or above.


Doctoral Students:
  All doctoral students should acquire any one of the following English Proficiency certifications before applying for the Dissertation Defense.
  The test date should be within 4 years prior to entering NDHU or while studying in NDHU.  Students must submit the original certification to verify.


TOEFL iBT score 79 and above (TOEFL paper version PBT/ITP score 550 and above) / 
TOEIC score 780 and above / 
GEPT (The General English Proficiency Test) High-Intermediate Level Second Stage, or   above (全民英檢，中高級複試以上)  / 
Other equivalent official English proficiency exams offered in/outside of NDHU campus. (See Appendix #1) 

Student may take the following English courses from either groups as the alternative of requirements:

Courses offered by the English Department, related to Listening, Communication, Oral Training, Reading, English Writing or Technical Writing, Composition,  Translating, or English for Science and Technology with 6 credits and graded B  or above.
Courses offered by the General Education Department, related to Listening, Communication, Oral Training, Reading, English Writing or Technical Writing, Composition, Translating, or English for Science and Technology, level (II) or above, with 6 credits and graded A-  or above.


This Requirement has been established by the Departmental Graduate Study Committee, approved by the Departmental Executive Meeting, announced and executed afterwards.  Any amendment should follow the same process accordingly.

",NDHU CSIE English Proficiency Requirement for Graduate Students  2013.05.07,05/21/2013 - 23:50,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/948,948,English
國立東華大學資訊工程學系研究生英語能力畢業標準實施辦法 2013.05.07,93,"國立東華大學資訊工程學系研究生英語能力畢業標準實施辦法
 
原文附載於研究所(碩、碩專、國際碩、博班)修業要點內
民國102年01月15日將其獨立
民國102年05月07日所務會議修訂
 
 

 為增進資訊工程學系研究生英語能力，提升其就業或繼續深造之競爭力，特訂定本英語能力畢業標準實施辦法。
 除取得英語系國家正式學位者，皆須取得下列任一種外語能力證明。(應檢附成績證明正本，且接受檢測日期須在入學前四年內或在學期間方為有效）。
碩士班部分(含資工碩士班、網多碩士班、與國際碩士班)：
  碩士班研究生在畢業之前，必須取得下列任一種之外語能力證明：
  （應檢附成績證明正本，且接受檢測日期須在入學前四年內或在學期間方為有效）。


托福iBT測驗61分以上 (紙筆托福TOEFL PBT/ITP 500分以上) /
多益 (TOEIC) 600分以上 /
全民英檢 (GEPT)中級複試或中高級初試以上 /
其他相對應之校內外英語能力檢定測驗。(如附件一)

本系認定之本校相關英文課程分2種課程：

英美系開設課程，應以聽講、溝通、閱讀、寫作、翻譯與習作、科技英文 相關，選修3學分，且成績須達 B-  以上。
通識教育中心開設課程，應以聽講、溝通、閱讀、寫作、翻譯與習作、科技英文 相關，程度二級（含以上），選修3學分，且成績須達 B+ 以上。


博士班部分：
  博士班研究生在申請論文考試之前，必須取得下列任一種之外語能力證明：
  (應檢附成績證明正本，且接受檢測日期須在入學前四年內或在學期間方為有效）。


托福iBT測驗79分以上 (紙筆托福TOEFL PBT/ITP 550分以上) / 
多益 (TOEIC) 780 分以上 / 
全民英檢 (GEPT) 中高級複試以上 / 
其他相對應之校內外英語能力檢定測驗。(如附件一) 

本系認定之本校相關英文課程分2種課程：：

英美系開設課程，應以聽講、溝通、閱讀、寫作、翻譯與習作、科技英文 相關，選修6學分，且成績須達 B 以上。
通識教育中心開設課程，應以聽講、溝通、閱讀、寫作、翻譯與習作、科技英文 相關，程度二級（含以上），選修6學分，且成績須達 A-  以上。


本畢業標準實施辦法由所務委員會擬定，經系務會議通過後公告實施，修正時亦同。

",國立東華大學資訊工程學系研究生英語能力畢業標準實施辦法 2013.05.07,05/21/2013 - 23:23,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/947,947,"Chinese, Traditional"
NDHU CSIE Regulation of the Primary Programming Proficiency (PPP) Certification 2013.05.07,93," The Latest Rule of PPP Certification had been updated to
 http://english.csie.ndhu.edu.tw/csieweb/en/node/1783 (2013.11.27) 

　　　　　　　　　　　　　　國立東華大學資訊工程學系基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Regulation of the Primary Programming Proficiency (PPP) Certification
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Department of Computer Science & Information Engineering
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　National Dong Hwa Universality 
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Approved by the Departmental Curriculum Designing and Planning Committee on 2012.09.06
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Approved by the Departmental Executive Committee on 2012.10.03
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Apply to undergraduate students (including International Bachelor classes) admitted on/after 2012 School year
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　Apply to graduate students (including International Graduate classes) admitted on/after 2013 School year
1.　　In order to ensure the students’ abilities on programming proficiency, and capacities of software development and implementation, this regulation has been established as a graduation requirement for all CSIE graduate and undergraduate students. 
2.　　Before graduation, each student is required to receive a PPP certificate by passing an on-site PPP test held each semester. The scope of the PPP test covers the comprehensive programming skills trained in the core courses including Introduction to Computer Programming (I) + (II), and Data Structures.  
3.　　There is no upper limit on the number of PPP tests a student can attend.
4.　　Students who want to participate in a PPP test must register in advance within two weeks of the beginning of each semester. The test will be scheduled in one month after the registration. The registration procedures will be posted on the departmental website.  
5.　　The PPP test will last three hours. Each participant should solve at least three problems to pass the test. 
6.　　Students may take any of the following contests/exams as an alternative of the PPP test. Students must submit their official certificate of the contests/exams to be considered as an alternative to the PPP certification.
　　　　i.　　  Receiving programming-related certificates approved by the PPP Certification Committee.
　　　　ii.　　 Participating in National Collegiate Programming Contest (NCPC) organized by the Minister Of Education (教育部舉辦全國大專電腦軟體設計競賽), ACM International Collegiate Programming Contest (ACM國際大學程式競賽), or other programming contests approved by the PPP Certification Committee, and receiving an award of “Excellent Work” or better.
　　　　iii.　　Participating the Collegiate Programming Examination (CPE大學程式能力檢定), and receiving a test score within the top 50% in that examination.
7.　　This Regulation has been established by the Departmental Curriculum Designing and Planning Committee, approved by the Departmental Executive Meeting, announced and executed afterwards.  Any amendment should follow the same process accordingly.
",NDHU CSIE Regulation of the Primary Programming Proficiency (PPP) Certification 2013.05.07,05/21/2013 - 23:10,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/946,946,English
國立東華大學資訊工程學系基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法 2013.05.07,93,"　　　　　　　　　　　　　　國立東華大學資訊工程學系基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法
註：已經有更新版--國立東華大學資訊工程學系基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法 2013.11.27   http://www.csie.ndhu.edu.tw/csieweb/zh-tw/node/1646 
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　101年9月6日課程暨學程規劃委員會議通過
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　101年10月3日系務會議通過
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　依101年10月3日系務會議決議，自101學年度起入學之學士班(含國際學士班)學生開始適用
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　自102學年度起入學之碩士班(含國際碩士班)學生開始適用
　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　102年5月7日所務會議建議辦法更名
第一條　　國立東華大學資訊工程學系（以下簡稱本系）為加強學生程式設計能力，並提昇軟體開發與專案製作之執行力，特訂定本「基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法」（以下簡稱檢定考）。
第二條　　檢定考以程式設計(一)、程式設計(二)及資料結構所教授內容為範圍，考試以上機實作方式進行。
第三條　　學生參加本檢定考沒有次數上之限制，可重覆參加至通過為止。
第四條　　同學於電腦教室實作程式，測驗結果將公佈於本系網頁，檢定時程為每學期開學後2周內報名，報名截止後一個月內施測，學生參加應試前必須先報名。
第五條　　學生應考成績以答對3題為通過，施測時間為三小時。
第六條　　本系學生符合下列條件者，得檢附相關證明文件，經本系程式能力檢定委員會通過者，視同通過本檢定考。
　　　　　　(1)　　取得本系核可之程式設計相關證照。
　　　　　　(2)　　參加教育部舉辦全國大專電腦軟體設計競賽、 ACM國際大學程式競賽或本系核可之程式競賽，成績在佳作以上。
　　　　　　(3)　　參加大學程式能力檢定(Collegiate Programming Examination, 簡稱CPE)，成績在當次測驗中排名前50%者。
第七條　　本辦法由課程暨學程規劃委員會擬定，經系務會議通過後公告實施，修正時亦同。
",國立東華大學資訊工程學系基本程式能力畢業標準實施辦法 2013.05.07,05/21/2013 - 23:01,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/945,945,"Chinese, Traditional"
