Doctoral Student Programming Planning 101 Year ,1,"101 Year NDHU CSIE Doctoral Student Programming Planning
一、Minimum Credit Requirement for Graduation:
　 Total: 34.0 credits
　 Professional Compulsary Courses:16.0 credits
　 Professional Elective Courses: 18.0 credits from courses,plus Thesis(I),(II),Seminar(III),(IV)
二、Important Rules and Regulations:

1. At least 1/2 of the courses must be from Department of Computer Science & Information Engineering.
2. Ph.D students may select any Master or Ph.D level courses to study, and the credits can be counted toward the graduation.
3. Credits earned on courses of the same name offered by other departments or institutes may be substituted (up to 9 credits maximum) toward elective course requirements with the approval of the Departmental Education Committee.
4. For NDHU master students, who directly continue their studies into doctoral program, must study at least 42 credits from the course list below.
5. Unless approved by advisor and departmental chairman, no repeated courses can be counted into the graduate credit twice.
6. For Ph.D students who continue their 3rd year, must select Thesis (III)~Thesis (XII) courses until graduation.  These credits will not be counted toward graduate credits.
7. All students must pass the English Proficiency Requirement for Graduate Students.

