國際碩士班101年課規,93,"


Computer Science and Information Engineering
Networking and Multimedia Technology



1. Graduation Requirements:Students must take a minimum of 28 graduate credit hours (including 4 credits of compulsory courses and 24 credits of elective courses), complete a thesis and pass a final oral examination on the thesis. 
2. Important Rules and Regulations (1) Students must take at least 12 credits from the elective courses offered by the CSIE Department.(2) Elective course credits of the Extensive Master Program of CSIE count toward graduation.(3) The minimum number of credit hours required for graduation is 28. A maximum of 12 credits may be waived on elective courses. (4) Second year and above students are required to take Seminar (III) & (IV) and Thesis (I) & (II). (5) Students may take the elective courses from the Master Program in Networking and Multimedia Technologies. Prior approval of the advisor is required. (6) Students whose native language is not English are required to fulfill the English Proficiency Requirement of the Graduate School before graduation. Please refer to the English Proficiency Certification Requirements of the CSIE Department for details.



