Department Atmosphere,1,"The Department of Computer Science and Information Engineering of National Dong Hwa University is young and full of vigorous atmosphere. The dynamic learning environment and state-of-the-art equipment are our distinguishing features. We endeavor to create a family-like atmosphere where teachers and students interact closely with each other. In our department, teachers devote themselves to teaching, and students invest efforts in professional learning.  All of us are like friends living together. Studying here is like joining a warm and welcoming academic family.
Our teachers pay close attention to cultivate students' independent thinking and creativity. The open learning space inspires a liberating academic ambiance.  The one-person-one-machine multimedia interaction computer labs, and campus-wide wifi services provide further support for students' learning.  The Department and the University ensure our students have the soundest learning experience and beyond students' expectations.
To facilitate the industrial development of the Eastern Taiwan region, National Dong Hwa University has been striving to drive High-Tech industries forward, and Information Engineering has been listed as one of the priorities.  To prepare our students for their future careers, our teaching emphasizes on both theory and practice, and we encourage students to participate in industrial programs during their free time.
",Department Atmosphere,06/15/2012 - 14:26,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/544,544,English
Chairman Speech,1,"Dear Students,
Welcome to the Department of Computer Science & Information Engineering (CSIE) of National Dong Hwa University (NDHU) !
This is your great opportunity and blessing to study in National Dong Hwa University.  The name “Dong Hwa” – stands for “the Eastern Elite of Taiwan”.  The university is well-known for its natural scenery, unique cultural heritage, vast campus, and pleasant learning environment.
Becoming a member of the Computer Science & Information Engineering (CSIE) Department is surely advantageous.  
All the teachers in our department are very active -- they spend much time and effort on their students, participate in departmental and social affairs, and are earnest in teaching and researching.
The implementation of the “family system” allows all students to have a close interaction with instructors and fellow family members.  This system ensures the caring and the sharing of life experiences, and reduces stresses from many aspects.  All faculty members participate in the departmental or university-level committees, which create communication paths for reflecting on students’ needs and suggestions to the department and school for future improvement. Our faculty members take their teaching jobs very seriously.  We have many systems, such as the course feedback, school counsel, and evaluation systems to ensure and improve the quality of teaching.  The faculty is also committed to enhancing the quality and the quantity of their research results, and to relate their research to course content.  
The Freedom of the Curriculum Program – since 2007, the Department and the University have adopted the “Curriculum Program"" system.  This system gives students the freedom to choose courses and programs according to their interests, the flexibility to arrange classes in cross-domain expertise, and the opportunity to deepen their knowledge.
In brief, the CSIE Curriculum includes the general requirements, core courses, and elective classes.  The core courses cover all important theories and fundamental knowledge of Computer Engineering.  The elective classes cover 2 major specialties—  Multimedia and Intelligent Computing, Network & System Design -- all very essential and popular professional fields. In addition to our own courses, students are free to select from campus-wide programs, and to study a minor or double-major.  When you graduate from this department, you will become competitive and confident, and be able to change society.
Besides the school work, there are many extra-curricular activities waiting for you.
Now is your time for growth and transformation. All faculty members and staff are ready to accompany you and to witness your bright future.  We enthusiastically await your arrival.
 
Sincerely,
 

Shiow-Yang Wu (吳秀陽), Ph.D., ProfessorChairmanDept. of Computer Science and Information EngineeringCollege of Science and EngineeringNational Dong Hwa UniversityHualien, Taiwan
2015.06.20
 
