Advantages 2. Testimony,1,"The Introduction from CSIE's 2014 Taiwan ICDF Scholarship Students

CSIE Vietnam Student Welcoming Speech

CSIE Indonesian Students Welcoming Speech

CSIE Mongolian Students Welcoming Speech

More NDHU。CSIE




Testimonial from Sambu (Gambia Student)
Receiving admission offer from National Dong Hwa University has been a happy and exciting moment for me. Initially I was wondering what part of the world I will be going to which is thousands of kilometers from my country. This has pushed me to go online to find out more information about Taiwan.  With all the difference in culture and education system between Gambia and Taiwan, frankly speaking, I am glad to come and feeling very comfortable to stay.
Though I did not travel much, the few countries I travelled to before and the ones I knew little about, to me, Taiwan is one of the safest countries to live. Since my arrival up-to-date, I have never seen a crime or heard about crime. Seeing school girls walking alone late at night definitely shows how secure and safe the environment is. Communication barrier has not been a problem, the local Taiwanese are ever ready to assist you in any way, to ensure your desire is achieved or problem in hand is solved.
It is so amazing to go around Hualien City and viewing its beautiful surroundings. Meeting new people has introduced me to whole new culture and tradition. The biggest difference I realized is the social life, which no two countries would have the same and I have to adjust myself to this situation. In terms of living expenditure, Taiwan requires more capital/money for daily life comparing to the Living Standard in Africa. Sometimes it is difficult to meet some demands; however, with the wonderful support from the university and the computer science department, I can happily say life is going good.
There is NO single day that I sat and felt regret to come to National Dong Hwa University for studying. I always tell my friends and family members that here is the best place to learn. The university is conducive to education, and it definitely provides amazing care and support for the students. The library and the laboratory are so equipped that the students can find more than they expect to learn. The dormitories are standard and well conducive to stay. Despite of cultural difference, NDHU students are very friendly and frequently hangout with other international students to explore the city and share lives together. Sport and recreation facilities are found every part of the campus and am definitely taking advantage of them especially football.
The wonderful supports and the continuous cares I am receiving from the Office of International Affairs (OIA) are amazing. They have been always there for me since the first day I arrived. The officers are very well trained and open to share with me and fellow international students. I am definitely feeling very comfortable to be within the Dong Hwa University’s family.
The NDHU’s Department of Computer Science & Information Engineering is the best and the most efficient department I have ever seen. The entire department is very caring and supportive. The administrative officers are always ready to solve our problems within their busy schedules. The professors are very knowledgeable and selfless to share with us. They provide the students all the courage, supports and tools we need to archive our objectives.  
I am very grateful to the whole Dong Hwa university staff especially the staff of the computer science department and the general student body for making the environment well pleasing and enjoyable for me.
A special thanks to you for being there for me.
Kind Regards
Sambu  2012.11.05

Testimonies from graudated students

LI, LUO-WEI, graduate of undergraduate and master programs, employee of a famous domestic game company
The department’s in-depth multimedia courses helped me build up my professional skills both theoretically and practically. I am able to analyze the situation when facing problem, and find out the solution quickly. Besides, I can acquaint myself fast with new technologies. If you plan to pursue your career in information industry, here is a good start to your success.
CHEN, CHANG-MING, graduate of master program, employee of a domestic company
After graduating from Dong Hwa’s CSIE, I was able to enter the field of 3D.  I learned the fundamental programming knowledge on speech recognition, image processing, and image pattern identification, which allowed me to participate in the development of 3D game when I returned to my position.
HU, SHI-JIE, graduate of master program, employee of a domestic company
The environment and the interactions between faculty and students are very supportive. The learning atmosphere among graduate and undergraduate students is vigorous. You can learn so much about the research and projects in your daily school life. And the solid project study really helps me deal with the challenges in workplace.
CHANG, SHU-WEI, graduate of undergraduate program, employee of a large technology company
Because technologies are always changing, you probably will not learn the hottest technologies while in school.  What NDHU’s CSIE teaches you is how to use the correct attitude to find the correct solution when you face technical problems. Here, they give you the fishing rod and teach you the skills, not just give you the fishes which you can buy anywhere in the market!
LU, JING-LAN, undergraduate exchange student from Mainland China
As an exchange student, I learned a lot during the one semester I stayed here.  The theories learning completed my knowledge on multimedia; the in-class exercises and experiments refined my pragmatic abilities; the communications with teachers and classmates broadened my horizon and understanding of the whole industry. All these experiences became my advantages that helped me entering my ideal graduate school.

