",碩士班,04/19/2012 - 16:31,/csieweb/zh-tw/depart/member/master,137,"Chinese, Traditional"
系學會,1,"東華資工系學會http://csiesa.csie.ndhu.edu.tw
",系學會,04/19/2012 - 16:16,/csieweb/zh-tw/about/org/csiea,136,"Chinese, Traditional"
Ph. D,1,"PHD
1.	Graduation Requirements:Students must take a minimum of 34 graduate credit hours (including 16 credits of compulsory courses and 18 credits of elective courses), complete a thesis and pass a final oral examination on the thesis.
2.	Important Rules and Regulations
(1)	Elective course credits of the Extensive Master Program of CSIE count toward graduation.
(2)	Third year and above students are required to take Thesis.
(3)	Students whose native language is not English are required to fulfill the English Proficiency Requirement of the Graduate School before graduation. Please refer to the English Proficiency Certification Requirements of the CSIE Department for details.
",Ph. D,04/19/2012 - 12:37,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/132,132,English
Master Program - Computer Sciense and Information Engineering,1,"Computer Sciense and Information Engineering
1.	Graduation Requirements:Students must take a minimum of 28 graduate credit hours (including 4 credits of compulsory courses and 24 credits of elective courses), complete a thesis and pass a final oral examination on the thesis.
2.	Important Rules and Regulations
(1)	Students must take at least 12 credits from the elective courses offered by the CSIE Department.
(2)	Elective course credits of the Extensive Master Program of CSIE count toward graduation.
(3)	The minimum number of credit hours required for graduation is 28. A maximum of 12 credits may be waived on elective courses.
(4)	Second year and above students are required to take Seminar (III) & (IV) and Thesis (I) & (II).
(5)	Students may take the elective courses from the Master Program in Networking and Multimedia Technologies. Prior approval of the advisor is required.
(6)	Students whose native language is not English are required to fulfill the English Proficiency Requirement of the Graduate School before graduation. Please refer to the English Proficiency Certification Requirements of the CSIE Department for details.
",Master Program - Computer Sciense and Information Engineering,04/19/2012 - 12:34,/csieweb/zh-tw/node/131,131,English
Undergraduate Program,1,"1.	All students must fulfill the General Education Requirements, complete four curriculum modules and take a minimum of 130 credits to graduate.
2.	Compulsory curriculum modules for Bachelor Degree in Computer Science and Information Engineering:
(1)	Foundation Module of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science (23 credits)
(2)	Core Module of Computer Science (I) (24 credits)
(3)	Core Module of Computer Science (II) (23 credits)
3.	Elective curriculum modules：
(1)	Multimedia (21 credits)
(2)	Networking and Computer Systems (21 credits)
(3)	Software Systems and Applications (21 credits)
(4)	Digital Life Technologies (21 credits)
4.	General Education: 43 credits (including Physical Education)
5.	Important Rules and Regulations
(1)	To graduate with a Bachelor Degree in Computer Science and Information Engineering, all students must fulfill the General Education Requirements, complete four curriculum modules (three compulsory, one elective) and take a minimum of 130 credits. The elective module can be any curriculum module offered by CSIE or other departments.
(2)	Students must take 6 credits in English and fulfill the English Proficiency Requirements by passing LTTC-GEPT (Intermediate or above) or meeting an equivalent criteria (including the certification issued by the Language Center).
(3)	No more than 9 credits of the Foundation Module may be counted toward the General Education Requirements.
(4)	Credits earned on courses of the same name offered by other departments or institutes may be counted toward degree requirements with the approval of the Education Committee.
(5)	The maximum credits per semester is 24 with the exception of Physical Education and Military Training. All other exceptions must receive prior approval by the Education Committee.
(6)	All Students must successfully complete Community Service Education (I) and (II) before graduation.
